1
00:02:01,521 --> 00:02:03,716
Easy! Steady up!

2
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:06,122
Hold on, mates!
He's almost up!

3
00:02:06,192 --> 00:02:08,888
That's it!
Give it a big pull!

4
00:02:08,995 --> 00:02:12,931
That's it! Don't drop him now!
Put your backs into it!

5
00:02:16,936 --> 00:02:18,870
Come on!

6
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:27,108
- [ Coughing ]
- There he goes. Lots of life in him.

7
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:30,616
Give it up, matey.
That's what you get for your trouble.

8
00:02:30,683 --> 00:02:32,844
Maybe he's just
taking a long swim.

9
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,944
Yeah, or a short flight.

10
00:02:35,021 --> 00:02:36,955
You an airman, mate?

11
00:02:37,023 --> 00:02:41,187
- He's not dressed like an airman.
- What kind of uniform is that, then?

12
00:02:41,261 --> 00:02:44,094
- [ Groans ]
-<i>Sprechen sie Deutsche? Jah?</i>

13
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:48,133
I say he's a rat
and we throw him overboard like a rat.

14
00:02:48,201 --> 00:02:50,135
Let's give him the heave-ho!

15
00:02:50,203 --> 00:02:52,671
[ Sailors Talking, Laughing ]

16
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:55,674
[ Mulder]
Hey.

17
00:02:55,742 --> 00:02:59,200
How's about another dip in
the Atlantic, huh? DirtyJerry.

18
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:01,474
Even the sharks won't eat him.

19
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:04,415
What you got to say for yourself,Jerry,
before we throw you back in?

20
00:03:04,484 --> 00:03:06,418
My name's notJerry.

21
00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,420
What's that?

22
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:10,422
My name's Mulder.
Fox Mulder.

23
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,390
That a name? Mulder?

24
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:14,392
I got I.D. in my pocket.

25
00:03:18,631 --> 00:03:21,930
"" Fox Mulder,
Federal Bureau of Investigation.""

26
00:03:22,001 --> 00:03:24,526
- Sorry, mate. Never heard of it.
- Never heard of it?

27
00:03:24,637 --> 00:03:27,606
Ever tell you what we do with foxes?
Care to know?

28
00:03:27,674 --> 00:03:29,232
You've never heard of the F.B.I.?

29
00:03:29,309 --> 00:03:32,403
Why don't you shut up,Jerry,
before we change our minds here.

30
00:03:32,478 --> 00:03:34,878
- Where are you taking me?
- Where'd you pick up that accent?

31
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:37,075
Probably in the Fuhrer's secret service.

32
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,345
- Come on.
- What are you talking about?

33
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:43,287
I say we cut him open and see
what color he bleeds. DirtyJerry.

34
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:46,120
<i>Deutschland uber alles.</i>
[ Spits ]

35
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:49,650
<i>[ Mulder ]</i>
Deutschland uber alles? <i>Wait a second.</i>

36
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,823
How's about you shove a cork
in it, mate. All right?

37
00:03:56,102 --> 00:03:58,036
[ Knocks ]

38
00:03:59,939 --> 00:04:01,930
Aye?

39
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:03,441
What's this about?

40
00:04:03,509 --> 00:04:05,568
Found him in the water, sir.

41
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:08,580
Don't know nothin' about him.
I think he's a German.

42
00:04:08,648 --> 00:04:10,548
Bring the prisoner in my room.

43
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,123
Friend or foe?

44
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:23,155
- What?
- To what flag do you pledge allegiance?

45
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:26,598
I think there's been a mistake.

46
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:29,601
I think the mistake is mine.

47
00:04:30,837 --> 00:04:32,771
Speak the truth, man.

48
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:34,773
- This is the <i>Queen Anne,</i> isn't it?
- Aye.

49
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:37,401
That's about enough of that.
I came looking for this ship.

50
00:04:37,477 --> 00:04:40,207
Say the word, Captain.
I'll make him the first of the rest.

51
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,215
- I think I can explain what's going on.
- It's a ruse, Captain.

52
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:44,682
What's our current position?

53
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:47,185
Cut the spy up.

54
00:04:47,253 --> 00:04:50,552
I'll tell you. We're two degrees
above the 30th Parallel.

55
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:53,217
Sargasso Sea,
just above the Tropic of Cancer.

56
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:56,922
64 degrees west by southwest
off the Plantagenet bank,

57
00:04:57,030 --> 00:05:00,124
60 miles south-southwest off Bermuda.

58
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:02,929
How would I know that
if I'd been in the water?

59
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:05,334
That's a damn good question, lad.

60
00:05:05,405 --> 00:05:07,373
I'm waiting for a damn good answer.

61
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,930
Tell me I'm wrong.

62
00:05:09,008 --> 00:05:11,203
Tell me that you haven't been able
to get accurate compass readings,

63
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:13,177
that navigation's been a real bitch.

64
00:05:13,246 --> 00:05:16,841
It's because you've been caught in
the Devil's Triangle. I can show you.

65
00:05:17,884 --> 00:05:19,977
It goes from Bermuda...

66
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:22,988
down to Puerto Rico, back up to Florida.

67
00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:25,650
The <i>Queen Anne</i> is stuck here
on the eastern edge of it.

68
00:05:25,725 --> 00:05:29,627
You've been caught in a time warp,
some kind of limbo dimension...

69
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:32,664
and now you've popped out
the other side into 1 998.

70
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,893
- 1 998?
- This man is mad.

71
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,935
Let him tell it to the fishes.

72
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:39,870
I'm done foolin' about, man.
There's a war on.

73
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:44,069
And in it or no, I don't plan
to lose me mind nor me ship...

74
00:05:44,143 --> 00:05:46,077
to the likes of a jackal like you.

75
00:05:46,145 --> 00:05:48,773
Relax. There's no war.
The world is at peace.

76
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:51,373
There's a little trouble over at our
White House, but that'll blow over.

77
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:53,385
So to speak.

78
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:56,616
Peace? It's September 3, 1 939, man.

79
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:58,213
Hitler's entered Poland...

80
00:05:58,291 --> 00:06:01,158
and we've just been boarded by a bunch
of his goose-stepping hooligans.

81
00:06:01,227 --> 00:06:04,094
So don't speak to me of peace, man.
Tell Mother England.

82
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:07,564
No, it's not September 3.
It's November 1 6. Look.

83
00:06:07,633 --> 00:06:10,101
-<i>[ Knocks On Door ] Excuse me, Captain.</i>
-<i>Aye.</i>

84
00:06:10,169 --> 00:06:13,468
Sir, the Germans, sir,
they've taken control of the bridge.

85
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:15,871
They're steering a course
for their homeland.

86
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:19,309
Not on the watch of Captain Yip Harburg,
they're not.

87
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:21,313
Lock the prisoner up in here.

88
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:25,510
It's okay. The war's over.

89
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:28,520
Let 'em take you to Germany.
They make nice cars.

90
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:34,559
This is unbelievable.

91
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,492
[ Static ]

92
00:06:45,104 --> 00:06:48,801
Mayday. Mayday. This is
Special Agent Fox Mulder with the F.B.I.

93
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,809
I'm on the S.S. <i>Queen Anne.</i>

94
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:52,742
[ Static Continues ]

95
00:06:52,812 --> 00:06:55,212
Ship in distress.
Mayday, mayday.

96
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:57,215
[ Announcer]
The British ambassador in Berlin...

97
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:59,808
handed the German government
a final note...

98
00:06:59,886 --> 00:07:02,081
stating that unless
we heard from them...

99
00:07:02,155 --> 00:07:06,091
that they were prepared at once
to withdraw their troops from Poland,

100
00:07:06,159 --> 00:07:08,855
a state of war would exist between us.

101
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,396
No such undertaking
has been received.

102
00:07:11,464 --> 00:07:15,628
Consequently, as of today,
September 3, 1 939,

103
00:07:15,701 --> 00:07:17,635
this country is at war with Germany.

104
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:19,398
Oh, sh--

105
00:07:19,472 --> 00:07:22,407
-<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>
-<i>[ Man Speaking German ]</i>

106
00:07:22,475 --> 00:07:24,409
[ Door Handle Rattling ]

107
00:07:24,477 --> 00:07:27,002
Hallo! Hallo!

108
00:07:28,981 --> 00:07:30,881
<i>Hallo?</i>

109
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:36,421
<i>[ Radio:Announcer ]</i>
<i>Closing places of entertainment.</i>

110
00:07:36,489 --> 00:07:40,721
<i>All cinemas, theaters</i>
<i>and other places of entertainment...</i>

111
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:44,752
<i>are to be closed immediately</i>
<i>until further notice.</i>

112
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,631
<i>The evacuation of British children...</i>

113
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:55,538
is going on smoothly and efficiently.

114
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:57,542
The ministry of health says--

115
00:07:57,610 --> 00:08:00,636
<i>[ Andrews Sisters ]</i>
& Bei Mir Bist Du Schon &

116
00:08:00,713 --> 00:08:03,443
<i>&Please let me explain &</i>

117
00:08:03,516 --> 00:08:05,916
& Bei Mir Bist Du Schon &

118
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:07,919
<i>&Means you're grand &</i>

119
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,921
[ Grunting ]

120
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,014
& Bei Mir Bist Du Schon &

121
00:08:12,091 --> 00:08:14,889
<i>&Again I'll explain &</i>

122
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:18,488
<i>&It means</i>
<i>you're the fairest in the land &</i>

123
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,032
What the hell is going on?

124
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,261
- Spender?
-<i>&I could say</i> bella, bella &

125
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,930
<i>&Even say</i> wunderbar &

126
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:29,668
<i>&Each language</i>
<i>only helps me tell you &</i>

127
00:08:29,742 --> 00:08:32,176
<i>&How grand you are &</i>

128
00:08:34,413 --> 00:08:35,846
<i>&Ree</i>-<i>dee &</i>

129
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,309
<i>&Ree</i>-<i>dee, ree</i>-<i>dee &</i>

130
00:08:39,385 --> 00:08:41,819
<i>&Ree</i>-<i>dee, ree</i>-<i>dee, ree</i>-<i>dee &&</i>

131
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:44,823
<i>&&[ Continues ]</i>

132
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:47,826
<i>[ Men Speaking In German ]</i>

133
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,135
[ German Continues ]

134
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:02,839
[ Man Shouts In German ]

135
00:09:04,076 --> 00:09:06,010
[ Continues Shouting ]

136
00:09:09,081 --> 00:09:10,981
[ All Shouting ]

137
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:12,570
<i>&&[ Woman Singing, Faint ]</i>

138
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:14,547
<i>&It's gotta be sunny to me &</i>

139
00:10:14,814 --> 00:10:17,408
<i>& When your eyes look into mine &</i>

140
00:10:17,483 --> 00:10:20,179
<i>&Jeepers creepers &</i>

141
00:10:20,252 --> 00:10:22,720
<i>& Where'd you get those peepers &</i>

142
00:10:27,226 --> 00:10:29,854
<i>& Gosh, oh, get up &</i>

143
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:32,489
<i>&How'd they get so lit up &</i>

144
00:10:44,677 --> 00:10:46,611
Hey.

145
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:49,477
<i>&Jeepers creepers &</i>

146
00:10:49,548 --> 00:10:51,948
<i>& Where'd you get those peepers &</i>

147
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:54,452
Excuse me.

148
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,454
Scully!

149
00:10:56,522 --> 00:10:59,457
Get your Nazi paws off me
before you get one in the kisser.

150
00:10:59,525 --> 00:11:02,392
- No, it's me, Mulder.
- Oh, you speak English, do you?

151
00:11:02,461 --> 00:11:04,486
Well, how'd you like to see
the stars in the American flag?

152
00:11:04,563 --> 00:11:07,691
- I'm not a Nazi.
- Sure. You just look like one, right?

153
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,735
I had to steal this uniform.

154
00:11:09,802 --> 00:11:12,236
[ Shouts In German ]

155
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:15,239
-<i>[ Gunshots ]</i>
- [ All Screaming ]

156
00:11:15,307 --> 00:11:18,242
[ Shouting In German ]

157
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:20,403
He said put your hands up.

158
00:11:21,647 --> 00:11:23,581
You see? I told you.

159
00:11:24,617 --> 00:11:26,710
<i>&&[ Resumes ]</i>

160
00:11:26,786 --> 00:11:28,879
<i>&Jeepers creepers &</i>

161
00:11:28,954 --> 00:11:31,889
<i>You're all big men now,</i>
<i>but wait until you get to Russia.</i>

162
00:11:31,957 --> 00:11:33,891
I hope you fellas like the cold!

163
00:11:33,959 --> 00:11:36,553
- Aah!
-<i>& Where'd you get those eyes &</i>

164
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:40,565
<i>& Gosh, oh, get up</i>
<i>How'd they get so lit up &&</i>

165
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:43,602
[ Men Shouting German ]

166
00:12:09,261 --> 00:12:11,695
[ Shouting Continues ]

167
00:12:21,607 --> 00:12:23,541
[ Shouts In German ]

168
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:25,543
Same to you, Adolf!.

169
00:12:25,611 --> 00:12:27,545
[ Continues Shouting ]

170
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:54,272
[ Speaking German ]

171
00:12:59,578 --> 00:13:02,012
I'll not give up this ship!

172
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:05,182
[ Speaking German ]

173
00:13:05,251 --> 00:13:07,685
Aye, you can put me down, man,

174
00:13:07,753 --> 00:13:10,688
but I'll not let go of this wheel.

175
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:12,690
So till we meet in hell--
[ Spits ]

176
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:16,694
[ German ]

177
00:13:16,762 --> 00:13:19,196
-<i>[ Gunshot ]</i>
-<i>[ Groans ]</i>

178
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:38,549
You.

179
00:13:38,617 --> 00:13:42,553
[ Speaking German ]

180
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,598
<i>No sprechen.</i>

181
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,600
[ Speaks German ]

182
00:13:55,701 --> 00:13:57,828
I don't speak Nazi.

183
00:13:57,937 --> 00:14:00,371
[ Continues In German ]

184
00:14:00,439 --> 00:14:05,308
Wait a minute. Why are you shooting me?
What have I done?

185
00:14:05,377 --> 00:14:08,813
I don't understand
what you're asking me.

186
00:14:08,881 --> 00:14:11,281
<i>[ Man ]</i> Halt!
<i>[ Speaking German ]</i>

187
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:27,299
[ Speaks German ]

188
00:14:28,801 --> 00:14:32,737
Skinner, where are they taking me?
Help me, Skinner!

189
00:14:38,844 --> 00:14:40,778
What are you guys doing here?

190
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:42,780
- Mulder's in trouble.
- Big trouble.

191
00:14:42,848 --> 00:14:45,248
- What do you mean?
- Let's take a walk.

192
00:14:45,317 --> 00:14:47,251
Okay. Where are we going?

193
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:49,253
The walls have ears.

194
00:14:49,321 --> 00:14:52,256
I have ears.
Tell me what's going on.

195
00:14:53,325 --> 00:14:55,418
- Mulder's disappeared.
- From where?

196
00:14:55,494 --> 00:14:57,428
From the National
Reconnaissance Office's...

197
00:14:57,496 --> 00:14:59,930
Lacrosse mid-latitude
imaging radar satellite.

198
00:15:02,935 --> 00:15:05,870
- What am I looking at?
- A whole lot of nothin'.

199
00:15:05,938 --> 00:15:08,907
We pulled that down 45 minutes ago
off the N.R.O. satellite,

200
00:15:08,974 --> 00:15:12,410
which early this morning
sent a picture of a ship...

201
00:15:12,478 --> 00:15:14,912
which inexplicably appeared
in the middle of the Atlantic.

202
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:17,881
The S.S. <i>Queen Anne,</i> which vanished
without a trace over 60 years ago.

203
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:20,384
- The British luxury liner.
- That's correct.

204
00:15:20,452 --> 00:15:22,886
- It was torpedoed by a German U-boat.
- That's one story.

205
00:15:22,955 --> 00:15:24,889
There's another?

206
00:15:24,957 --> 00:15:26,390
Though her exact position
was kept a secret...

207
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:27,891
for fear spies might
give her up to the Axis,

208
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,894
it's been determined
that the <i>Queen Anne...</i>

209
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,396
was just south of the Plantagenet bank
when she went missing.

210
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:34,898
Less than 60 feet of water,
yet she's never been found.

211
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:37,902
- The <i>Queen Anne</i> just disappeared?
- Into the Bermuda Triangle.

212
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:42,236
- And reappeared this morning at 6:49.
- That's impossible.

213
00:15:42,341 --> 00:15:44,775
- The satellite doesn't lie.
- There's nothing on here.

214
00:15:44,843 --> 00:15:47,778
We gave the original images to Mulder so
he could use them as navigational aids.

215
00:15:47,846 --> 00:15:49,780
- He was in a hurry.
- To get where?

216
00:15:49,848 --> 00:15:52,248
Out to the <i>Queen Anne</i>
before anyone else got there first.

217
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:55,253
- He's gone out here?
- He chartered a powerboat.

218
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:58,256
We tracked him on the satellite
for an hour and a half.

219
00:15:58,324 --> 00:16:00,258
Until a storm blew in
and obscured all transmissions.

220
00:16:00,326 --> 00:16:02,191
- That's what you're holding.
- What's happened to him?

221
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:04,695
We can't know that,
not without alternative tracking data.

222
00:16:04,763 --> 00:16:06,697
Which is why we're here.

223
00:16:06,765 --> 00:16:10,201
- All we can do is hope for the best.
- But expect the worst.

224
00:16:10,269 --> 00:16:12,203
Well, we have to get help.

225
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:15,536
- He's a needle in a haystack.
- What do you need?

226
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,575
[ Sighs ]

227
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:22,080
Navy AWACS S.L.A.R or S.A.R.
1 00K swath imaging.

228
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:25,548
You're gonna have to find somebody
at the Pentagon to get it.

229
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:27,551
Wait for me downstairs.

230
00:16:35,627 --> 00:16:37,561
I need to speak with him.

231
00:16:37,629 --> 00:16:39,563
- Could you take a seat--
- Is he in?

232
00:16:39,631 --> 00:16:42,065
- Yes, he's on his phone.
- This can't wait.

233
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:44,068
Sir?

234
00:16:44,136 --> 00:16:45,694
Hold on a minute.

235
00:16:45,804 --> 00:16:47,237
What is it, Agent Scully?

236
00:16:47,306 --> 00:16:49,331
I just received some
very disturbing information, sir.

237
00:16:49,441 --> 00:16:51,375
I need your help.

238
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:53,377
I'll call you back in five.

239
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:57,681
You can't come rushing in here.

240
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,685
Sir, I couldn't waste time
explaining myself to your assistant.

241
00:17:00,753 --> 00:17:04,120
- Tell me what is so urgent.
- Agent Mulder's done something rash.

242
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,453
- I can't.
- He may be lost at sea.

243
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,459
- I can't, Agent Scully.
- You can't what?

244
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:11,963
- I can't help you.
- This isn't for me. It's for Mulder.

245
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:14,966
My hands are tied.
I'm not your direct superior any longer.

246
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:17,969
- Don't you want to know about this?
- No, I don't.

247
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:21,495
- I don't even want to hear it.
- Sir, this is about a man's life.

248
00:17:21,573 --> 00:17:25,737
I'm not allowed to have any contact
with either you or Mulder.

249
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:27,745
She walked right past me, sir.

250
00:17:30,749 --> 00:17:32,683
You're out of line, Scully.

251
00:17:32,751 --> 00:17:34,685
No, sir, <i>you're</i> out of line.

252
00:17:34,753 --> 00:17:38,689
I'm sorry, but I'm coming to you for
help and I've got nowhere else to go.

253
00:17:38,757 --> 00:17:41,191
I would hope that after
everything we have been through...

254
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:44,696
you'd at least have the courtesy, the
decency, not to mention the respect...

255
00:17:44,763 --> 00:17:47,197
to listen to what I have to say.

256
00:17:47,266 --> 00:17:49,530
All I need is information.

257
00:17:49,601 --> 00:17:52,536
You don't have to do anything else.

258
00:17:55,641 --> 00:17:59,907
Look, sir, if you know anybody
at the Office of Naval Intelligence,

259
00:17:59,978 --> 00:18:02,173
it would be of great help.

260
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:07,618
I could lose my job, my pension.

261
00:18:07,686 --> 00:18:10,621
I could even be subject to legal action.

262
00:18:10,689 --> 00:18:12,623
[ Sighs ]

263
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:17,094
Use your head, Scully.

264
00:18:17,162 --> 00:18:19,096
It'll save your ass.

265
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:22,324
Save your own ass, sir.

266
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:24,835
You'll save your head along with it.

267
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:37,381
[ Sighs ]

268
00:19:03,609 --> 00:19:05,543
Ouch.

269
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:07,545
Sorry.

270
00:19:26,098 --> 00:19:29,534
<i>Yes, sir, I'll get those files and</i>
<i>buzz you when I have him on the line.</i>

271
00:19:29,601 --> 00:19:32,536
- <i>I need a word with A.D. Kersh.</i>
- I'm sorry. He's not available.

272
00:19:32,638 --> 00:19:35,573
Uh, Assistant Director Kersh,
may I please have a moment of your time?

273
00:19:35,641 --> 00:19:37,575
A moment for what?

274
00:19:37,643 --> 00:19:39,577
May I, sir? Thank you.

275
00:19:41,813 --> 00:19:45,044
Sir, I need you
to get me some information.

276
00:19:45,117 --> 00:19:48,052
I am not at liberty to say why,

277
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:51,055
but I can tell you
it is of the utmost importance.

278
00:19:53,292 --> 00:19:55,226
<i>Yes?</i>

279
00:19:55,294 --> 00:19:57,228
I, uh-- Sorry.

280
00:19:57,296 --> 00:19:59,696
I-I shouldn't have come unannounced.

281
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:04,068
May I see what you were
going to show me, Agent Scully?

282
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:07,138
Uh, it wa--

283
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:09,640
It's nothing,

284
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,642
really.

285
00:20:12,911 --> 00:20:14,845
Good.

286
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:33,764
[ Sighs ]

287
00:20:33,832 --> 00:20:36,767
What am I thinking?
What am I thinking?

288
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:39,837
[ Beeps, Dialing ]

289
00:20:39,938 --> 00:20:42,372
Sorry.

290
00:20:42,441 --> 00:20:44,375
[ Line Ringing ]

291
00:20:51,183 --> 00:20:54,118
Come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

292
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:56,120
Answer, Mulder.

293
00:20:56,188 --> 00:20:59,123
- Answer the phone, answer the phone.
- [ Ringing Continues ]

294
00:21:00,859 --> 00:21:02,724
Come on, Mulder.

295
00:21:02,794 --> 00:21:06,230
[ Phone ] The cellular customer you
are trying to reach is not responding.

296
00:21:06,298 --> 00:21:08,232
Damn.

297
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:15,773
I want you to do me a favor.

298
00:21:15,841 --> 00:21:19,777
It's not negotiable. Either you do it
or I kill you. You understand?

299
00:21:21,179 --> 00:21:23,113
- You okay, Agent Scully?
- No, I'm not.

300
00:21:23,181 --> 00:21:26,742
I'm a gun ready to go off, so don't
even think about trying to weasel me.

301
00:21:26,818 --> 00:21:28,752
What is it that you need?

302
00:21:30,055 --> 00:21:32,319
Navy AWACS...

303
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:34,450
S.L.A.R.

304
00:21:34,526 --> 00:21:38,462
1 00K swath south-southeast of Bermuda.

305
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:42,261
I am looking for a boat, maybe a ship.
1 939 luxury liner.

306
00:21:42,334 --> 00:21:44,268
- 1 939?
- Don't ask too many questions.

307
00:21:44,336 --> 00:21:47,271
I don't care what you do or who you do
or who you have to grease.

308
00:21:47,372 --> 00:21:50,307
I need that information
and I need it now. Are we clear on that?

309
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:52,309
Crystal.

310
00:21:52,377 --> 00:21:55,312
<i>And Agent Spender,</i>
<i>if you're not back in a hurry,</i>

311
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:58,781
- I'll hunt you down and so help me--
- Right.

312
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,984
[ Sighs ]
God.

313
00:22:04,056 --> 00:22:05,990
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

314
00:22:08,126 --> 00:22:10,060
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

315
00:22:11,797 --> 00:22:14,891
-Hello.
-[ Cigarette-Smoking Man ] Agent Fowley?

316
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:18,231
- Yes.
- I was looking for Agent Spender.

317
00:22:18,303 --> 00:22:22,262
He's not here right now.
Is there something I can help you with?

318
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:25,276
Agent Scully just handed the
assistant director a piece of paper...

319
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:28,279
with an intelligence system
scribbled on it--

320
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:32,215
Yes?

321
00:22:32,284 --> 00:22:34,718
- Yes, sir?
- Who is this?

322
00:22:43,495 --> 00:22:45,429
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

323
00:22:46,598 --> 00:22:48,532
- [ Gasps ]
- Agent Scully.

324
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:51,034
- I was just--
- I was sent to come get you.

325
00:22:51,103 --> 00:22:53,037
I was waiting for Agent Spender.

326
00:22:53,138 --> 00:22:55,572
I'm supposed to pick up
a delivery from him.

327
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:58,575
Agent Spender is with
Assistant Director Kersh.

328
00:22:58,643 --> 00:23:00,577
That rat bastard.

329
00:23:10,188 --> 00:23:12,122
Stupid--

330
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:14,124
-<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>
- Scully!

331
00:23:14,192 --> 00:23:16,626
[ Static ]
...Scully...

332
00:23:16,695 --> 00:23:18,629
Mulder, is that you?

333
00:23:18,697 --> 00:23:20,631
[ Static Continues,
<i>V</i>oice Breaking Up ]

334
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:24,968
No, I can't--
I'm on an elevator.

335
00:23:25,036 --> 00:23:27,470
Hold on, I'll be off in a s--

336
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:29,506
Hold on.

337
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,580
<i>[ Static Continues,</i>
<i>Voice Breaking Up ]</i>

338
00:23:37,649 --> 00:23:39,583
- Hello?
- ...Scully...

339
00:23:39,651 --> 00:23:41,585
No--

340
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:45,689
I can't understand!

341
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:48,191
I can't--

342
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:50,194
- Was that you?
- Is that you?

343
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:53,197
I've been trying to reach you.
I got the information you needed.

344
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:57,301
How?

345
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:59,303
Don't even ask.

346
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:01,339
Sir, what you've done--

347
00:24:01,406 --> 00:24:03,772
Is save Mulder's ass.
I know.

348
00:24:03,842 --> 00:24:06,777
And if you ever ask me
to break policy or protocol,

349
00:24:06,845 --> 00:24:09,780
I will have you tossed
out of the F.B.I. for good.

350
00:24:09,848 --> 00:24:11,748
- Am I understood, Agent Scully?
- Yes.

351
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:17,888
Yes!

352
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:19,890
[ Sighs ]

353
00:24:33,672 --> 00:24:35,731
[ Tires Screech ]

354
00:24:40,011 --> 00:24:41,945
<i>[ Byers ]</i>
<i>Did you get it?</i>

355
00:24:42,013 --> 00:24:43,947
Yeah.

356
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:45,915
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>

357
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:57,494
<i>Oi, American, right?</i>

358
00:24:57,562 --> 00:24:59,496
Saved your life, mate.

359
00:24:59,564 --> 00:25:02,431
Krauts don't want no reason
to bring you Yanks into the war.

360
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:05,436
-I got two words for you-- Pearl Harbor.
-What?

361
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:08,439
After Poland, Hitler's on his way
to Denmark, Holland and France...

362
00:25:08,507 --> 00:25:10,441
with a few stops in between.

363
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:13,444
The French all but roll over on us,
the Italians seize their opportunity,

364
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:15,946
and theJapanese
come through the back door.

365
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:18,915
It's a long, bloody story.
Fortunately, it has a happy ending.

366
00:25:18,984 --> 00:25:22,420
- We win.
- With no small amount of help from us.

367
00:25:22,487 --> 00:25:26,253
Not much to apologize over the next
50 years, except for the Spice Girls.

368
00:25:26,324 --> 00:25:28,792
<i>[ Shouting In German ]</i>

369
00:25:37,636 --> 00:25:39,570
Well, according to our host,

370
00:25:39,638 --> 00:25:42,072
this'll be our new
accommodations, lads.

371
00:25:42,140 --> 00:25:45,075
You speak German.
What was that shouting about up there?

372
00:25:45,143 --> 00:25:48,078
They got it in mind that we left America
carrying arms to England.

373
00:25:48,146 --> 00:25:50,046
Are we?

374
00:25:50,115 --> 00:25:53,551
Listen, she's drawing 1 6 feet
at 81 ,000 tons.

375
00:25:53,618 --> 00:25:56,212
We're making 21 knots at full power.

376
00:25:56,288 --> 00:25:59,849
If we got munitions aboard this ship,
they don't weigh but a few stone.

377
00:25:59,925 --> 00:26:03,326
The captain knew something.
He wouldn't give up the wheel.

378
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:06,831
The Nazis boarded us after
they intercepted a radio communication.

379
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:09,833
Some kind of code word
they keep asking about--

380
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:11,835
Thor's Hammer.

381
00:26:11,903 --> 00:26:13,837
You know what that is, mate?

382
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:15,839
<i>Who goes there?</i>

383
00:26:15,907 --> 00:26:17,841
<i>I said, who goes there?</i>

384
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:20,844
Show your face,
or we'll bloody beat them to a stub.

385
00:26:20,912 --> 00:26:23,847
<i>Put your irons down, boys.</i>
<i>It's your own crew, for God's sake.</i>

386
00:26:23,915 --> 00:26:26,816
- What are you doin' down here?
- Havin' a cup of tea.

387
00:26:26,885 --> 00:26:29,319
What's it look like,
you stupid swabbo?

388
00:26:29,387 --> 00:26:31,321
Then who's steerin' the boat?

389
00:26:31,389 --> 00:26:34,324
Just some blokes who answer
to the name of ""<i>Heil Hitler.</i> ""

390
00:26:34,426 --> 00:26:38,362
Ever been to Germany? They'll have a
special affection for the likes of you.

391
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:40,864
<i>Hey, this ship can't go to Germany!</i>

392
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:42,866
Make up your mind, mate.

393
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:47,200
It can't. You're not carrying munitions.
It's something far more deadly.

394
00:26:47,272 --> 00:26:50,207
- Thor's Hammer.
- Thor's Hammer is a man, not a weapon.

395
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:53,767
A man who will help build a bomb
that'll win the war for whoever has it.

396
00:26:53,845 --> 00:26:57,508
- You're saying he's aboard this ship?
- I saw him. In the ballroom.

397
00:27:04,155 --> 00:27:06,089
<i>[ Guard Speaking German ]</i>

398
00:27:06,157 --> 00:27:08,125
[ Speaking German ]

399
00:27:12,097 --> 00:27:15,032
<i>Auf weidersehen,</i> mates.

400
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:19,036
What's wrong with you? Don't you know
there are spies everywhere?

401
00:27:19,104 --> 00:27:21,538
Trust no one, man!

402
00:27:21,606 --> 00:27:24,040
We've got to stop this ship! Now!

403
00:27:24,109 --> 00:27:27,044
- All right, lads, let's go!
- [ Sailors Shouting ]

404
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:35,752
<i>Hey,you, who's in charge</i>
<i>of this engine room?</i>

405
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:38,755
[ Shouting Continues ]

406
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:40,757
Hey, I'm talking to you.

407
00:27:40,859 --> 00:27:43,293
Shut her down, man.
We've got to scuttle her now!

408
00:27:43,361 --> 00:27:45,295
Put some piss in her, boys.

409
00:27:45,363 --> 00:27:48,799
You heard him! Kill the engines!
There's no other way, swabbo!

410
00:27:48,867 --> 00:27:51,802
You can't get to Germany
if you can't steer.

411
00:27:51,870 --> 00:27:54,805
Me overriding her.
We steering a course for home.

412
00:27:54,873 --> 00:27:56,807
Have you looked at your compass?

413
00:27:56,875 --> 00:27:59,309
You can't get to England
going the wrong bloody direction.

414
00:27:59,377 --> 00:28:02,744
We're not going to England.
We're going toJamaica.

415
00:28:02,814 --> 00:28:04,714
Steer her home, you bloody ruffo,

416
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:06,717
to her home where she belongs.

417
00:28:06,785 --> 00:28:09,720
Listen to me!
You can't take this ship to England!

418
00:28:09,788 --> 00:28:12,723
- You'll never make it!
- What are you talking about?

419
00:28:12,791 --> 00:28:14,884
There's only one place
she's going, Yank.

420
00:28:14,993 --> 00:28:16,927
-Jamaica!
- [ Cheering, Shouting ]

421
00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:18,929
You can't take the ship
toJamaica either.

422
00:28:18,997 --> 00:28:21,932
The Germans will hunt you down
no matter what course you steer.

423
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,934
- No! No!
- Hear it out! Hear it out!

424
00:28:24,002 --> 00:28:25,936
And who you be, boy?

425
00:28:26,004 --> 00:28:28,438
- My name's Mulder.
- He wants to go back to bloody America.

426
00:28:28,506 --> 00:28:31,441
No, I don't. I want you to
turn this ship around the way you came.

427
00:28:31,509 --> 00:28:33,443
- [ All Shouting ] No! No!
- Bloody hell!

428
00:28:33,511 --> 00:28:35,445
We're halfway home!

429
00:28:35,513 --> 00:28:37,413
You've got to turn the ship around!

430
00:28:37,482 --> 00:28:39,416
- And what's in that direction?
- The future.

431
00:28:39,484 --> 00:28:41,918
- <i>What?</i>
- Actually, the past.

432
00:28:41,986 --> 00:28:43,920
Oh, well, I'm convinced.

433
00:28:43,988 --> 00:28:45,922
I can explain it to you.

434
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:48,959
<i>[ Soldier ]</i>
Du! Der Amerikaner!

435
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:51,461
<i>[ Continues In German ]</i>

436
00:28:52,630 --> 00:28:54,564
Turn the ship around,

437
00:28:54,632 --> 00:28:56,566
or Hitler rises, Germany wins...

438
00:28:56,634 --> 00:29:00,070
and your children will never know
what freedom is!

439
00:29:02,073 --> 00:29:03,174
[ Shouting In German ]

440
00:29:03,174 --> 00:29:04,903
[ Shouting In German ]

441
00:29:16,855 --> 00:29:18,789
Halt!

442
00:29:18,857 --> 00:29:21,792
<i>Halt!</i>
[ Continues Shouting In German ]

443
00:30:06,271 --> 00:30:08,535
<i>Achtung!</i>

444
00:30:14,112 --> 00:30:16,046
<i>Aufstehen.</i>

445
00:30:17,182 --> 00:30:20,117
<i>Mach schnell.</i>
Get up!

446
00:30:26,457 --> 00:30:29,893
[ Speaking German ]

447
00:30:42,974 --> 00:30:46,410
There's a scientist on board
who can make a bomb.

448
00:30:46,477 --> 00:30:48,411
Who is this man?

449
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:50,379
I don't know.

450
00:30:50,448 --> 00:30:52,382
[ Continues Speaking German ]

451
00:31:03,094 --> 00:31:05,028
You will answer the question...

452
00:31:05,096 --> 00:31:07,530
or we will begin killing passengers.

453
00:31:08,733 --> 00:31:11,167
Which one is the scientist?

454
00:31:12,337 --> 00:31:14,271
I don't know.

455
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:18,375
[ Continues In German ]

456
00:31:27,518 --> 00:31:29,486
[ Passengers Gasp ]

457
00:31:33,458 --> 00:31:35,392
- [ Gunshot ]
-<i>[ Passengers Screaming ]</i>

458
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:37,394
<i>[ Body Falls ]</i>

459
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,838
[ Continues In German ]

460
00:31:50,808 --> 00:31:53,743
How many lives
are you willing to sacrifice?

461
00:31:56,814 --> 00:31:59,214
None.

462
00:31:59,284 --> 00:32:01,218
Then you have the answer.

463
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:07,624
[ Speaking German ]

464
00:32:12,497 --> 00:32:15,625
-<i>[ Pistol Cocks ]</i>
- [ Passengers Gasp ]

465
00:32:15,700 --> 00:32:17,634
-<i>[ Gunshot ]</i>
- [ Screaming ]

466
00:32:17,702 --> 00:32:19,636
<i>[ Scully ]</i>
<i>Stop!</i>

467
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:21,695
This man has no answers.

468
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:24,708
You're killing innocent people
to learn that he knows nothing!

469
00:32:24,776 --> 00:32:27,210
Shut up.
Shut up and move away.

470
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:29,212
Listen to me, you little weasel--

471
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:31,180
[ Speaking German ]

472
00:32:37,288 --> 00:32:39,518
[ Passengers Gasping, Murmuring ]

473
00:32:39,624 --> 00:32:41,558
<i>[ Continues In German ]</i>

474
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:48,965
Answer the question.

475
00:32:49,033 --> 00:32:51,126
I'll answer the question.

476
00:32:56,808 --> 00:32:59,743
<i>[ Cigarette</i>-<i>Smoking Man</i>
<i>Continues Speaking German ]</i>

477
00:33:01,079 --> 00:33:03,104
That man is the scientist.

478
00:33:18,463 --> 00:33:20,397
<i>[ Frohike ]</i>
<i>Hey, Scully.</i>

479
00:33:20,465 --> 00:33:23,400
<i>You're not gonna believe this.</i>
<i>Get up here.</i>

480
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:25,402
<i>What?</i>

481
00:33:26,971 --> 00:33:29,405
<i>The sky just cleared,</i>
<i>and there it was.</i>

482
00:33:30,641 --> 00:33:32,734
Is it the <i>Queen Anne?</i>

483
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:34,744
<i>[ Byers ]</i>
<i>That's her.</i>

484
00:33:36,814 --> 00:33:38,714
I don't believe it.

485
00:33:38,783 --> 00:33:40,717
Seeing is believing.

486
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:45,889
They've got power.

487
00:33:47,658 --> 00:33:50,092
<i>[ Byers ]</i>
<i>Maybe Mulder's already on board.</i>

488
00:33:50,161 --> 00:33:52,095
Let's hope he is.

489
00:33:53,831 --> 00:33:55,765
You're lying.

490
00:33:55,833 --> 00:33:58,097
- He's telling the truth.
- Shut up!

491
00:33:58,169 --> 00:34:01,263
- Who is the scientist?
- I told you, this man is the scientist.

492
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:03,273
[ German ]

493
00:34:11,849 --> 00:34:14,784
- [ Speaks German ]
- What is the man's name?

494
00:34:16,621 --> 00:34:18,555
John Brown.

495
00:34:18,656 --> 00:34:21,090
Ask me again,
and I'll knock you down.

496
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:23,093
- What's his name?
- Puddintame!

497
00:34:23,161 --> 00:34:25,595
Ask me again,
I'll tell you the same.

498
00:34:25,663 --> 00:34:27,597
<i>Wait. Don't shoot.</i>

499
00:34:29,667 --> 00:34:31,601
I'm the scientist.

500
00:34:31,669 --> 00:34:34,103
- This man's a liar.
-<i>[ Man Shouts In German ]</i>

501
00:34:34,172 --> 00:34:36,106
- <i>I'm</i> the scientist.
- Please.

502
00:34:36,174 --> 00:34:39,109
Tell them the truth
before someone else has to die.

503
00:34:39,177 --> 00:34:41,611
- I don't know this man.
- Don't listen to her.

504
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:44,580
She's traveling with me to protect me.
She works for the O.S.S.

505
00:34:44,649 --> 00:34:47,083
- [ Speaks German ]
- [ Soldiers Shouting In German ]

506
00:34:48,319 --> 00:34:50,753
[ Continues Speaking German ]

507
00:34:50,822 --> 00:34:52,756
[ Whispers ]
That's great.

508
00:34:52,857 --> 00:34:55,291
I don't see you did any better.

509
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:04,367
[ Continues Speaking German ]

510
00:35:09,941 --> 00:35:12,375
- What'd he say?
- [ Soldiers Continue Shouting ]

511
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:19,272
- I think I know what he said.
- You learn fast.

512
00:35:19,350 --> 00:35:21,784
<i>[ Soldier Shouting In German ]</i>

513
00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:29,725
<i>[ Engines Winding Down ]</i>

514
00:35:31,963 --> 00:35:34,898
- What's happening?
- The engines shut down.

515
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,874
<i>[ Shouting, Screaming ]</i>

516
00:36:55,646 --> 00:36:57,546
- Hey!
- Hey what?

517
00:36:57,615 --> 00:36:59,549
- Come with me.
- Why should I?

518
00:36:59,617 --> 00:37:02,643
'Cause you're the only one
who can save this ship.

519
00:37:26,611 --> 00:37:28,545
Come on.

520
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:33,516
<i>[ Soldier Shouting In German ]</i>

521
00:37:34,919 --> 00:37:36,853
[ Continues Speaking German ]

522
00:37:43,127 --> 00:37:45,061
Now what, Einstein?

523
00:37:46,797 --> 00:37:49,061
<i>[ Shouts In German ]</i>

524
00:37:49,133 --> 00:37:51,067
<i>[ Gunshot ]</i>

525
00:37:51,135 --> 00:37:53,069
<i>[ Body Falls ]</i>

526
00:37:59,410 --> 00:38:02,345
God bless America.
Now get your asses out of here.

527
00:38:24,368 --> 00:38:26,302
<i>[ Scully ]</i>
<i>Byers?</i>

528
00:38:26,370 --> 00:38:29,305
-<i>[ Soldiers Shouting In German ]</i>
- Langly?

529
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:32,575
Frohike?

530
00:38:44,588 --> 00:38:46,522
Come on. Come on.

531
00:38:55,132 --> 00:38:57,066
There you guys are.

532
00:40:01,298 --> 00:40:01,866
What are you doing?

533
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:03,231
What are you doing?

534
00:40:03,300 --> 00:40:05,734
- Telling you how to save this ship.
- Out here?

535
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:08,067
I can't stay.
I gotta get back to history.

536
00:40:08,139 --> 00:40:10,733
- What?
- You gotta rescue it. Listen to me.

537
00:40:10,808 --> 00:40:13,242
The ship's caught in something
called the Devil's Triangle--

538
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:15,244
a time warp, a rift in space.

539
00:40:15,312 --> 00:40:17,712
- Are you crazy?
- You know Einstein, right?

540
00:40:17,782 --> 00:40:19,716
He predicts the theoretical possibility.

541
00:40:19,784 --> 00:40:22,218
He also predicts an atomic weapon
that will destroy the world.

542
00:40:22,286 --> 00:40:24,220
Yeah? So what?

543
00:40:24,288 --> 00:40:26,222
If you don't convince the crew...

544
00:40:26,323 --> 00:40:28,757
to turn this ship around and head
back into the Devil's Triangle,

545
00:40:28,826 --> 00:40:31,386
everything Einstein predicted
will become true...

546
00:40:31,495 --> 00:40:33,929
except for the outcome of history.

547
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:37,633
So if I don't turn this ship around--

548
00:40:38,736 --> 00:40:41,170
In all likelihood, I won't exist.

549
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:45,105
And neither will you.

550
00:40:45,176 --> 00:40:47,110
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

551
00:40:47,178 --> 00:40:49,112
So, in case we never meet again--

552
00:41:04,795 --> 00:41:06,729
[ Gasps ]

553
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:10,233
I was expecting a left.

554
00:41:12,803 --> 00:41:14,737
Hey!

555
00:41:31,555 --> 00:41:33,489
<i>[ Splash ]</i>

556
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:55,278
<i>[ Voices Overlapping ]</i>

557
00:42:12,930 --> 00:42:14,557
<i>[ Scully ]</i>
<i>Mulder?</i>

558
00:42:16,133 --> 00:42:19,102
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>

559
00:42:19,169 --> 00:42:21,103
Mulder, it's me.

560
00:42:22,806 --> 00:42:24,740
- Where am I?
- You're in a hospital.

561
00:42:24,808 --> 00:42:26,742
- Oh...
- Lie still.

562
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:28,744
I feel...

563
00:42:28,812 --> 00:42:30,712
like hell.

564
00:42:30,781 --> 00:42:33,716
I don't blame you. You've been
through the wringer, I'd say.

565
00:42:33,784 --> 00:42:35,718
What happened to me?

566
00:42:35,786 --> 00:42:38,949
You did something incredibly stupid.

567
00:42:39,023 --> 00:42:40,957
What did I do?

568
00:42:41,025 --> 00:42:43,459
You went looking for a ship, Mulder,

569
00:42:44,695 --> 00:42:46,629
in the Bermuda Triangle.

570
00:42:47,965 --> 00:42:50,399
- Say that again?
- [ Frohike ] Gilligan awakes.

571
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:54,270
You were there.

572
00:42:54,338 --> 00:42:56,272
You were there, Scully.

573
00:42:56,340 --> 00:42:58,774
- He's delirious.
- And he was there too.

574
00:42:58,842 --> 00:43:00,776
Right, me and my dog Toto.

575
00:43:00,844 --> 00:43:02,709
You were there with the Nazis.

576
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:04,680
Mulder, settle down.
It's an order.

577
00:43:04,748 --> 00:43:06,682
- Not that he takes orders.
- Yeah.

578
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:08,718
- You saved the world, Scully.
- Yeah.

579
00:43:08,786 --> 00:43:10,720
You're right. I did.

580
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:13,222
- What kind of drugs is he on?
- I want some.

581
00:43:13,290 --> 00:43:16,225
No, no, the <i>Queen Anne.</i> I found it.
You were there with Thor's Hammer.

582
00:43:16,293 --> 00:43:19,228
I told you you had to turn the ship
around, then I jumped overboard.

583
00:43:19,296 --> 00:43:23,858
I bet you did. The boat you were on
was busted into a million pieces.

584
00:43:23,968 --> 00:43:26,095
And as for the <i>Queen Anne,</i>

585
00:43:26,203 --> 00:43:28,637
it was nothing more
than a ghost ship.

586
00:43:28,706 --> 00:43:32,642
No, no, no, you and I
were on that ship, Scully,

587
00:43:32,710 --> 00:43:34,803
in 1 939.

588
00:43:35,879 --> 00:43:37,779
Get some rest, Mulder,

589
00:43:37,848 --> 00:43:41,284
'cause when you get out of here,
I'm gonna kick your butt but good.

590
00:43:42,820 --> 00:43:44,754
Come on. Let's go.

591
00:43:44,822 --> 00:43:47,416
I would've never seen you again.

592
00:43:47,491 --> 00:43:49,425
But you believed me.

593
00:43:51,795 --> 00:43:53,729
In your dreams.

594
00:43:55,399 --> 00:43:58,368
Mulder, I want you to close your eyes...

595
00:43:58,435 --> 00:44:01,302
and I want you to think to yourself,

596
00:44:01,372 --> 00:44:03,306
""There's no place like home.""

597
00:44:03,374 --> 00:44:05,308
[ Chuckles ]

598
00:44:06,477 --> 00:44:08,411
Hey, Scully.

599
00:44:11,949 --> 00:44:13,883
Yes?

600
00:44:18,188 --> 00:44:20,418
I love you.

601
00:44:20,491 --> 00:44:23,051
Oh, brother.

602
00:44:23,127 --> 00:44:25,061
[ Sighs ]

603
00:45:14,978 --> 00:45:16,680
<i>[ Child ]</i>
<i>I made this!</i>

604
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:19,672
<i>[ Child ]</i>
<i>I made this!</i>

